Changelog
==================

All notable changes to this project will be documented in here.

The format is based on https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/).

[2.3] 2025-02-26
--------------------------
Added
- Documentation (sphinx and readthedoc)
- New repository

Deleted
- Cleaning some files and functions not useful anymore

[2.2.2] - 2025-02-13
--------------------------

Fixed
- Bug of some Invalid polygons in matching step
- Some MultiPolygons were not separated in separated Polygons during the loading of data
- Vulnerability of Fiona
- The tests-pipeline is now correctly plugged to the main branch

Added
- Few documentation (comments in the code)
- GNU GPL License

[2.2.1] - 2024-09-11
--------------------------
Changed
- Clean example directory with examples (script, data and configuration) for both 2D and 3D cases

Added
- Initialisation of a github pipeline and automatic tests of Pyscoring


[2.2.0] - 2024-07-09
--------------------------
Added
- A first integration of 3D metrics in pyscoring (for CityJSON files)
- Possibility to use a config file to configurate a launch of pyscoring

Fixed
- Clean the example launching script 


[2.1.1] - 2024-04-09
--------------------------
Changed
- Print time inside the pyscoring interfaces, not anymore in the example
- Time in h : m : s 

Fixed
- Parallelisation inside by pyscoring interfaces
- Back to previous match method
- Choice of the working-bbox
- Output files creation

[2.1.0] - 2024-03-13
--------------------------
Added
- Starting using interface inside pyscoring to configure, load data and launch metrics computers
- First tries of using .log in the output
- Possibility to use a shapefile to define a working bbox
- More configurations : criteria, threshold, families of metrics, log, wbbox, output choice

Changed
- Make example file shorter and using the first instance of pyscoring's interface

Fixed
- Matches 

[2.0.6] - 2024-03-08
--------------------------
Added
- An output file in .shp
- A proposition of QGIS style for the output .shp to analyse output
- Integration of the function to merge metrics in pyscoring (from example script)
- Metrics by category of matches in the output
- Add extended match (union of building over the match) for special cases in the matching system

Changed
- Column names of local outputs to fit the restriction of 10 characters
- Ids listed in local output with "," between them and not "/n"


[2.0.5] - 2024-01-19
--------------------------
Added
- Matching possible with IOU threshold now

Changed
- Update matching classes and files

[2.0.4] - 2024-01-17
--------------------------
Added
- Max value of Edges metrics for Contour (distance) and Orientation (angle differences) 
- Informations of P (Prediction) or GT (GroundTruth) for the Edges metrics

Fixed
- Debug Orientation in some cases

Changed
- Only 2 decimal numbers in local metrics

[2.0.3] - 2023-11-21
--------------------------
Added
- Possibility to merge buildings (N-M) 

Fixed
- Earthpy not usable offline, replaced by Pyproj

[2.0.2] - 2023-10-02
--------------------------
Added
- Example script with a parallelisation
- CSV output local metrics : with id and local metrics
- CSV output global metrics 

[2.0.1] - 2023-09-29
--------------------------
Changed
- Initialisation of Pyscoring 2.0

